    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverioTacc"/>, <citedRange>XV.67</citedRange></bibl> and
                    <bibl><ptr target="#antiTacc"/>, <citedRange>VII.15</citedRange></bibl>, whence,
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>127</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#laronde1987"/>, pp. <citedRange>54, 121</citedRange> (photo)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>098000</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            <p>Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/>, p. <citedRange>103</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65032"><name nymRef="#Μνάσαρχος">Μνάσαρχος</name></persName> 
                    <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64259"><name nymRef="#Θεύχρηστος" type="patronymic">Θεοχρήστω</name></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><rs type="office" key="eponymous priest"><w lemma="ἱαριτεύω">ἱαριτέυων</w></rs> <w lemma="ἀνατίθημι">ἀνέθηκε</w>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="1"><lem resp="#laronde1987">Θεοχρήστω</lem>
                <rdg resp="#SECir">Θευχρήστω</rdg>
                </app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Mnasarchos fils de Theοkhrèstos a consacré <supplied reason="subaudible">ce monument</supplied> durant sa prêtrise.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Mnasarchos son of Theοchrestos dedicated <supplied reason="subaudible">this monument</supplied> while being priest.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Mnasarchos figlio di Theοchrestos ha dedicato <supplied reason="subaudible">questo monumento</supplied> quando era sacerdote.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>For the family of the dedicant, see <bibl><ptr target="#laronde1987"/>, pp. <citedRange>54, 121</citedRange></bibl>, who dated the inscription down to ca. 225 BC.
                <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/></bibl> in turn dates it back to 270/260 BC.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
